      "content": "# Comprehensive Guide to the User Profile Endpoint: GET /user\n## 1. Endpoint Introduction and Functionality\nThis section details the primary purpose of the `/user` endpoint.\n### 1.1 Core Functionality Description\nIt serves as the definitive retrieval mechanism for the currently authenticated user's profile data.\n#### 1.1.1 Authentication Prerequisite\nAccess requires a valid, active session token.\n## 2. Request Specification Deep Dive\nThis section meticulously outlines how the request must be constructed.\n### 2.1 HTTP Method Details\nThe required method is `GET`.\n### 2.2 URI Path Definition\nThe specific path to target is `/user`.\n#### 2.2.1 Path Parameters (None)\nNo path parameters are accepted for this operation.\n## 3. Response Schema and Data Contract\nThis covers the expected structure of the data returned upon success.\n### 3.1 Successful Response Code\nThe expected status code is `200 OK`.\n#### 3.1.1 Payload Structure\nThe body adheres to a defined JSON schema.\n##### 3.1.1.1 Field: `id`\nThe unique, immutable identifier",
